    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "After `reposix-sim` crashes mid-session, the FUSE daemon hangs indefinitely on the next `ls` call.\n\nReproduction steps:\n1. Start `cargo run -p reposix-sim`\n2. Mount: `cargo run -p reposix-fuse -- /tmp/mnt`\n3. Kill the sim: `kill -9 $(pgrep reposix-sim)`\n4. Run `ls /tmp/mnt` — blocks forever\n\nExpected: FUSE should return `EIO` within the configured timeout.\n\n```\nthread 'main' panicked at 'called Result::unwrap() on Err value: reqwest::Error { kind: Request, source: hyper::Error(Connect) }'\n```\n\nThe `reqwest` client never times out. The mount point requires `fusermount -uz /tmp/mnt` to recover.",
