    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "The `bench_token_economy.py` script currently calls the Anthropic API on every run, which is unnecessary when the fixture files have not changed.\n\n**Proposal:** Add a `--offline` flag that reads cached `*.tokens.json` sidecar files instead of making live API calls. The cache key should be a SHA-256 hash of the fixture content so stale entries are detected automatically.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- `python3 scripts/bench_token_economy.py --offline` completes in <2 s with no network calls.\n- If a fixture's bytes differ from the cached `content_hash`, the script exits non-zero with a helpful error message.\n- CI always passes `--offline`; only developers with `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` can regenerate the cache.\n\nRelated: BENCH-01 from REQUIREMENTS.md.",
